events.name: Manmade Disaster and Rescue
events.description: A disaster caused by humans and the subsequent rescue.

events.name: Manmade Disaster
events.ta1explanation: A disaster caused by humans.

events.name: Rescue
events.ta1explanation: Rescuing the victims from the disaster.

events.name: Investigation
events.ta1explanation: Investigation of cause of the disaster.

events.name: Civil Justice
events.ta1explanation: Justice procedures on those responsible for the disaster.

events.name: collapse
events.ta1explanation: Collapse of a building etc., in a disaster
events.description: engineering event in which the structural integrity of a construction iscompromised due to failure of components of the structure

events.name: conflagration
events.description: large and destructive fire that threatens human life, animal life, health, and/or property
events.ta1explanation: An area or building is set on fire.

events.name: trap
events.ta1explanation: victims are trapped in the disaster site
events.description: use of a device to remotely catch an animal

events.name: damage
events.description: changes introduced into a system that adversely affect its current or future performance
events.ta1explanation: Damage caused to buildings at the disaster site.

events.name: injury
events.description: physiological wound caused by an external source
events.ta1explanation: Victims are injured by the disaster.

events.name: death
events.description: permanent cessation of vital functions
events.ta1explanation: Victims die from the disaster.

events.name: announcement
events.description: printed, spoken, or published statement or notice of an event or other news
events.ta1explanation: government announces the disaster to public

events.name: command
events.description: message conveying a requirement to perform a certain action
events.ta1explanation: government commands rescuers to carry out rescue

events.name: communication
events.description: act of conveying intended meanings from one entity or group to another through the use of mutually understood signs and rules
events.ta1explanation: rescuers communicate with trapped victims

events.name: emergency_evacuation
events.description: urgent movement of people away from the threat or actual occurrence of a hazard
events.ta1explanation: rescuers evacuate trapped victims

events.name: collaboration
events.description: working together
events.ta1explanation: different parties of rescuers collaborate

events.name: transport
events.description: human-directed movement of things or people between locations
events.ta1explanation: rescuers transport victims to medical sites

events.name: treatment
events.description: attempted medical remediation of a health problem, usually following a diagnosis
events.ta1explanation: medical treatment of the victims

events.name: recover

events.name: death
events.description: permanent cessation of vital functions
events.ta1explanation: Patients die post treatment.

events.name: Identifycategorize
events.description: cognitive process in which ideas and objects are recognized, differentiated, and understood
events.ta1explanation: Investigation of a manmade disaster includes identifying its initiators.

events.name: Contact
events.ta1explanation: Make contact with the suspect

events.name: Arrest
events.ta1explanation: Taking the suspect who caused the disaster into custody
events.description: detention of a person and taking it into custody, usually because it has been suspected of committing or planning a crime

events.name: Handcuffing
events.ta1explanation: Using handcuffs to secure a suspect who initiated the disaster.
events.description: restraint devices

events.description:
interviewing employed by law enforcement officers, military personnel, 
and intelligence agencies with the goal of eliciting useful information

events.name: Restrain
events.ta1explanation: Physical restraint on the suspect

events.name: Inspect
events.ta1explanation: Organized examination or formal evaluation on the initiator of the disaster.
events.description: organized examination or formal evaluation exercise, often involving themeasurements, tests, and gauges applied to certain qualitycharacteristics in comparison with specified requirements or standards
